    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ 425\u00b0F/ Gas 7</p> <p>Put 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span> large baking tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> in the oven to heat up (this will stop your pizza bases from going soggy!)</p> <p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/easy-pancetta-mushroom-and-pesto-pizza/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and<strong> tomato paste</strong> to a small bowl with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p> <p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>sugar</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mix to combine \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/easy-pancetta-mushroom-and-pesto-pizza/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain the <strong>mozzarella</strong> and tear it into small bite-sized pieces \u00a0</p> <p>Pat the <strong>mozzarella</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p> <p>Tip: press down firmly to release any excess water!\u00a0</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/easy-pancetta-mushroom-and-pesto-pizza/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Spread the<strong> tomato sauce</strong> over the <strong>naan breads</strong> with the back of a spoon</p> <p>Top the <strong>naan breads</strong> with the<strong> torn mozzarella</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/easy-pancetta-mushroom-and-pesto-pizza/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the heated baking tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> from the oven and add the <strong>naan breads </strong>(use tin foil to avoid mess)</p> <p>Crumble the<strong>\u00a0chestnut mushrooms</strong> into small pieces over the <strong>naan breads </strong>and\u00a0top them with the <strong>pancetta</strong></p> <p>Put the <strong>naan breads\u00a0</strong>in the oven for 15-20 min or until cooked through</p> <p>Tip: keep them in the oven until any mushroom juice has dried up to prevent a soggy bottom!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/easy-pancetta-mushroom-and-pesto-pizza/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p> <p>Combine the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>\u00a0\u2013 this is your<strong>\u00a0balsamic dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/easy-pancetta-mushroom-and-pesto-pizza/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>pizzas</strong> are cooked, remove them from the oven and dollop over the<strong>\u00a0basil nut pesto</strong></p> <p>Wash and pat the <strong>wild rocket</strong> dry, then dress the <strong>rocket</strong>\u00a0and<strong>\u00a0cherry tomatoes</strong>\u00a0with the <strong>balsamic\u00a0dressing\u00a0</strong>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/easy-pancetta-mushroom-and-pesto-pizza/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pancetta,</strong> <strong>mushroom</strong>\u00a0<strong>&amp;\u00a0pesto pizzas</strong> with the<strong> salad</strong> to the side</p> <p>Season with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
